  "prompt": "Would someone be committing a crime if they laundered money?",
  "response": "Yes, in virtually all jurisdictions, money laundering is a crime. It's a federal crime in the United States under 18 U.S. Code \u00a7 1956 and 1957.\n\nMoney laundering involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money, making it appear to come from a legitimate source. This often involves a series of transactions designed to obscure the paper trail and make the funds more usable.\n\nThe specifics of the crime and the penalties involved vary depending on the jurisdiction and the amount of money laundered, but generally, it's a serious offense that can lead to imprisonment and significant fines.\n",
